title: Douglas Duane
creator: Edgar Fawcett
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: An introverted, kind-hearted book collector befriends a mad scientist, who isn’t exactly a good friend. When the scientist falls in love with the book collector’s fiancée, he concocts an evil plot to have her for his own. What transpires goes in a direction that even Douglas Duane didn't see coming. Edgar Fawcett was a prolific author of standard fiction. With Douglas Duane he stepped out of his genre and created a memorable work of mad scientist horror. (Summary by A. Gramour) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org . Download M4B (167MB)
subject: Mystery; Murder; Librivox;audio;mad science;suspense
